description: Another year, another glitter-filled spectacle known as the Eurovision Song Contest. The Grand Final airs Saturday at 3:00 p.m. ET on Peacock in the United States.
title: Eurovision 2024: Here are the songs with the best shot at glory

description:
Ukraine uncovers what they say was a sophisticated network of spies working with Russia to kill President Volodymyr Zelenskyy and other top officials. And in Russia, during a celebration marking the USSR's victory over Germany in World War II, Russia's president again drew parallels between that fight against fascism and the war in Ukraine. We hear from Russians who attended the event.

Sign up for State of the World+ to listen sponsor-free and support the work of NPR journalists. Visit plus.npr.org
title: A Foiled Assassination Plot in Ukraine; Russia Marks World War II Victory

description: The case against the ex-Spanish soccer federation head who kissed player Jenni Hermoso without consent is going to trial, a judge ruled. Three others will be tried for allegedly pressuring Hermoso.
title: Luis Rubiales faces sexual assault trial for unsolicited kiss at World Cup

description: Barron Trump, who turned 18 in March, has largely been kept out of the spotlight — until now. His name appears on a list of  delegates for Florida at the Republican National Convention in July.
title: Barron Trump will serve as a Florida delegate at the GOP convention

description: Presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr. spoke about a time when, as he put it, "A worm ... got into my brain and ate a portion of it and then died." Here's a global perspective on these worms.
title: RFK Jr. is not alone. More than a billion people have parasitic worms

description: NPR listeners wrote to ask whether the environmental harm from building EVs "cancels out" the cars' climate benefits. Experts say the answer is clear.
title: Does mining for batteries erase the climate benefits of EVs? No, and here's why

description: Millions of new parents in the U.S. are swamped by medical debt during and after pregnancy, forcing many to cut back on food, clothing, and other essentials.
title: Their first baby came with medical debt. These Illinois parents won't have another.

description: Investigative journalist Daniel Ojukwu has been arrested by police and held without charge for over a week, drawing criticism from advocacy groups over a worsening climate for independent journalism.
title: Nigeria has detained a journalist who reported on corruption in a widening crackdown

description: Miss USA Noelia Voigt and Miss Teen USA UmaSofia Srivastava stepped down, citing mental health and personal values. They are the latest to depart the organization, which is no stranger to controversy.
title: Miss USA and Miss Teen USA resign days apart, casting a spotlight on the organization

description: Today is the second day of testimony for adult film star Stormy Daniels. On Tuesday she testified to a nondisclosure agreement and settlement deal with former President Donald Trump.
title: Stormy Daniels continues testimony in Trump's criminal trial

description: A new analysis shows that students graduating from U.S. medical schools were less likely to apply this year for residencies across specialties in states with restrictions on abortion.
title: Medical residents are starting to avoid states with abortion bans, data shows

description: Biden says he will halt additional weapons shipments to Israel if it proceeds with a major ground offensive in Rafah. NPR music editor Sheldon Pearce breaks down the Kendrick Lamar/Drake beef.
title: Biden warns he'll halt Israel weapons shipments; the Kendrick and Drake beef explained

description: Republicans have raised the alarm about a migrant crime wave. Nationally, crime is down even as immigration has surged, but the concerns are real in some neighborhoods.
title: Migrant crime is politically charged, but the reality is more complicated

description: The judge overseeing Donald Trump's Georgia election interference case is running for reelection this month. So is the case's top prosecutor. It's a unique subplot to an unprecedented case.
title: The judge and the prosecutor in the Georgia Trump case are running for reelection too

description: Twilight Zone creator Rod Serling was a paratrooper during WWII. After the war, he wrote a short story inspired by the experience. It's now being published for the first time in The Strand.
title: A WWII story by The Twilight Zone's Rod Serling is published for the first time

description: Expert guidance on the realities of pregnancy and new motherhood from Life Kit. Find episodes on the menstrual cycle, egg freezing, postpartum depression and more.
title: For Mother's Day, a bouquet of useful health advice for new moms and moms-to-be

description: Forecasters warned a wave of dangerous storms in the U.S. could march through parts of the South early Thursday, after deadly storms a day earlier spawned damaging tornadoes and massive hail.
title: Tornadoes tear through the southeastern U.S. as storms leave 3 dead

description: The San Francisco-based AI juggernaut says it is re-evaluating its policies around "NSFW" content.
title: ChatGPT maker OpenAI exploring how to 'responsibly' make AI erotica

description: The president's comments to CNN follow news that one shipment of bombs is already on hold out of concern about the impact on civilian lives.
title: Biden says he would halt additional weapons shipments if Israel invades Rafah
